WEBVTT

00:03.300 --> 00:04.667
- WITH INTEREST RATES
BEING WHAT THEY ARE,

00:04.700 --> 00:06.400
WE THINK THIS IS EXACTLY
THE RIGHT TIME TO STRIKE

00:06.433 --> 00:08.600
WITH A CASINO COMPLEX
OF THIS MAGNITUDE.

00:08.633 --> 00:10.033
OR AS THEY SAY IN MACAU...

00:10.033 --> 00:12.633
[speaking Mandarin]

00:12.667 --> 00:14.100
[laughter]
SO...

00:14.133 --> 00:15.200
[cell phone vibrates]

00:15.233 --> 00:16.400
- EMMA IS OUR BEST
AND BRIGHTEST.

00:16.433 --> 00:17.767
- OH.

00:18.000 --> 00:21.166
- SO REST ASSURED, YOU ARE
IN THE MOST CAPABLE OF HANDS.

00:21.200 --> 00:22.367
- NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,
I'M SO SORRY.

00:22.400 --> 00:23.567
I JUST HAVE A PLANE
TO CATCH.

00:23.567 --> 00:25.300
PLEASE CONTACT MY CELL.

00:25.300 --> 00:26.467
MY ASSISTANT HAS IT.

00:26.500 --> 00:28.400
AND, AGAIN,
BEEN AN HONOR WORK WITH YOU.

00:28.433 --> 00:29.400
- OH, WAIT.
- YES.

00:29.433 --> 00:30.400
- ONE MORE THING.

00:30.433 --> 00:32.467
MR. ZHANG PRESENTS
CHINESE SCROLL.

00:32.500 --> 00:33.467
- OH, I REALLY COULDN'T.

00:33.500 --> 00:34.567
- PLEASE.
- IT'S TOO MUCH.

00:34.567 --> 00:35.700
OH, NO, IT'S REALLY--
- I INSIST.

00:35.734 --> 00:37.100
- OH, PLEASE, IT'S--
- YOU MUST.

00:37.133 --> 00:38.600
- OKAY, THANK YOU.

00:38.633 --> 00:41.133
THANK YOU VERY MUCH
AND TAKE CARE.

00:41.166 --> 00:43.533
- OH, HE ALSO HAS
ANOTHER SCROLL FOR YOU.

00:43.567 --> 00:45.100
- OH, WOW,
ANOTHER SCROLL.

00:45.133 --> 00:46.734
- CHINESE SCROLL.
- OH, THANK YOU.

00:46.767 --> 00:48.200
THIS IS JUST--
I'LL TREASURE IT.

00:48.200 --> 00:50.000
PLEASE THANK MR. ZHANG
FOR ME.

00:50.033 --> 00:51.133
OKAY.
- WAIT.

00:51.166 --> 00:52.133
- YO.

00:52.166 --> 00:53.266
- THERE'S ONE MORE SCROLL.

00:53.300 --> 00:54.400
- IS THERE?
OKAY.

00:54.433 --> 00:56.367
- CHINESE SCROLL.
- OH, WOW!

00:56.400 --> 00:59.266
THIS IS LIKE THE CLIFFSNOTES
EDITION, RIGHT?

00:59.300 --> 01:01.033
ALL RIGHT,
WELL, THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

01:01.066 --> 01:05.200
LOOK FORWARD
TO SEEING YOU ALL AGAIN.

01:05.200 --> 01:06.200
HELLO?
- WHERE ARE YOU?

01:06.233 --> 01:07.266
DO NOT LIE TO ME.

01:07.300 --> 01:08.266
- I'M ON THE PLANE.

01:08.300 --> 01:10.066
YES,
I WOULD LIKE SOME MORE NUTS.

01:10.100 --> 01:11.066
THANK YOU.

01:11.100 --> 01:12.200
- YOU'RE STILL
AT THE OFFICE.

01:12.233 --> 01:13.266
- I'M LEAVING RIGHT NOW.

01:13.300 --> 01:14.600
I JUST GOT STUCK
IN THE PRESENTATION

01:14.633 --> 01:15.734
OF THE WORLD'S TINIEST SCROLL.

01:15.767 --> 01:17.033
JUST DO SOMETHING
WITH THOSE.

01:17.066 --> 01:18.266
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
TO DO WITH THEM.

01:18.300 --> 01:20.000
- I SWEAR TO GOD, IF YOU ARE
NOT ON THIS FLIGHT--

01:20.033 --> 01:21.300
- WHAT AM I, A MONSTER?

01:21.333 --> 01:22.633
I'M GONNA MISS
MY BEST FRIEND'S BABY SHOWER?

01:22.633 --> 01:24.500
COME ON NOW.
[drill whirring]

01:24.533 --> 01:26.667
HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DRILLING?
IT IS 3:00 A.M. IN CONNECTICUT.

01:26.700 --> 01:28.767
- I'M JUST MAKING SOME
MINOR CRIB MODIFICATIONS.

01:28.767 --> 01:30.633
- HEY, BOB VILA,
YOU'RE EIGHT MONTHS PREGNANT.

01:30.633 --> 01:32.200
SO WHY DON'T YOU LET
YOUR HUSBAND DO THAT?

01:32.233 --> 01:34.233
- HE'S SNOOZING, AND ALSO,
I JUST WANT THIS BABY GIRL

01:34.233 --> 01:36.233
TO KNOW THAT HER MAMA'S
NOT AFRAID TO PICK UP A DRILL

01:36.233 --> 01:37.633
AND GET DOWN.

01:37.633 --> 01:39.066
- I WILL SEE YOU IN 18 HOURS,

01:39.100 --> 01:40.367
YOU AND THAT BABY
YOU'RE COOKING.

01:40.400 --> 01:42.300
- I'M GONNA HUG YOU SO HARD,
IT'S GONNA HURT.

01:42.333 --> 01:43.633
- I'M GONNA SQUEEZE YOU
SO HARD,

01:43.633 --> 01:45.100
THAT BABY'S GONNA
COME OUT OF YOU.

01:45.100 --> 01:46.266
OH!

01:46.300 --> 01:48.266
- HOW YOU FORGET
YOUR SCROLLS?

01:48.300 --> 01:49.500
- OH, MY GOSH.

01:49.500 --> 01:51.367
WHERE DID--I THOUGHT
THEY WERE IN MY CARRY-ON.

01:51.400 --> 01:53.233
- EMMA, GET OUT OF THERE!

01:53.266 --> 01:54.367
- PRESENTATION
OF CHINESE SCROLLS.

01:54.367 --> 01:55.500
- CHINESE SCROLL.
I GET IT, OKAY.

01:55.500 --> 01:56.667
- GET OUT OF THERE!
- PRESENTATION, YES...

01:56.700 --> 01:58.100
- GET OUT OF CHINA! OKAY.
- OF THE CHINESE--

01:58.133 --> 02:00.266
- BACK AWAY FROM
THE ELEVATOR, SIR!

02:00.300 --> 02:01.500
[Back Before We Were Brittle
by Say Hi playing]

02:01.533 --> 02:05.266
- ♪ HEY, REMEMBER WHEN ♪

02:05.300 --> 02:08.467
♪ ALL OF TIME STOOD STILL ♪

02:08.500 --> 02:10.667
♪ DO DO DO DO ♪

02:10.667 --> 02:13.066
♪ OOH ♪

02:13.100 --> 02:16.133
♪ BACK BEFORE
WE WERE BRITTLE ♪

02:16.166 --> 02:20.767
♪ BACK BEFORE WE WERE
BRITTLE ♪

02:21.000 --> 02:23.266
- I CANNOT BELIEVE THAT YOU
ARE IN MY CAR RIGHT NOW.

02:23.266 --> 02:25.567
- I CAN'T BELIEVE WHAT A
STUNNING PREGNANT WOMAN YOU ARE.

02:25.600 --> 02:27.133
- OH, PLEASE, I'M HUGE.

02:27.133 --> 02:28.700
- NO, I WILL TELL
YOU WHAT'S HUGE,

02:28.734 --> 02:30.533
AND THAT IS THESE
MAMMER-JAMMERS.

02:30.567 --> 02:31.734
THEY GO ALL NIGHT.

02:31.767 --> 02:33.734
THEY'RE LIKE THE BOOBS
OF OUR DREAMS!

02:33.767 --> 02:35.133
MAY I FEEL THEM?
- YEAH, GET IN THERE.

02:35.133 --> 02:36.567
- OH, G--HMM.

02:36.600 --> 02:38.533
YOU KNOW WHAT'S INTERESTING?
- WHAT'S THAT?

02:38.567 --> 02:40.200
- IS I THOUGHT THEY'D BE SOFT.
- UH-HUH.

02:40.233 --> 02:41.767
- BUT THEY'RE ACTUALLY
QUITE FIRM TO THE TOUCH.

02:42.000 --> 02:43.066
- WELL, THEY'RE FILLING
WITH MILK.

02:43.100 --> 02:44.567
- THEY'VE GOT A REAL HEFT
TO THEM.

02:44.600 --> 02:46.166
LIKE A WATER BED ALMOST.
HEY, HEY, HEY.

02:46.166 --> 02:47.266
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- WHAT?

02:47.300 --> 02:48.433
- PLEASE DON'T GO DOWN
MAIN STREET.

02:48.433 --> 02:49.767
- I JUST WANT YOU
TO SEE WHAT'S CHANGED.

02:50.000 --> 02:51.333
- NO, NOTHING'S CHANGED.
EVERYTHING'S ALWAYS THE SAME.

02:51.367 --> 02:53.700
- THEY PLANTED PLUM TREES.
- OH, GOD.

02:53.700 --> 02:56.433
- OH, AND A NICE PAKISTANI
FAMILY TOOK OVER WILSON DRUGS.

02:56.467 --> 02:58.367
- WHY IS EVERYONE WAVING AT US?

02:58.400 --> 02:59.700
HEY.
- WHAT'S THAT?

02:59.700 --> 03:01.400
- I'M GONNA TELL YOU WHAT
I'M NOT INTERESTED IN.

03:01.433 --> 03:02.433
- ♪ PLEASE ♪

03:02.467 --> 03:03.767
- AND THAT'S ONE
MR. KENNY LOGGINS.

03:04.000 --> 03:05.100
- ♪ CELEBRATE ME HOME ♪

03:05.133 --> 03:06.467
- I DON'T WANT TO SEE ANY
OF THESE PEOPLE.

03:06.500 --> 03:07.767
- ♪ GIVE ME A NUMBER ♪

03:08.000 --> 03:09.400
- I DIDN'T EVEN TELL MY MOM
I WAS COMING HOME.

03:09.433 --> 03:10.667
- ♪ CELEBRATE ME HOME ♪

03:10.700 --> 03:12.233
- THIS PLACE MAKES ME FEEL
LIKE I CAN'T BREATHE.

03:12.266 --> 03:13.500
DO YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?
I JUST CAN'T BREATHE.

03:13.533 --> 03:16.066
- ♪ PLAY ME ONE MORE SONG,
Y'ALL ♪

03:16.100 --> 03:17.433
I LOVE THAT PART.
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

03:17.433 --> 03:19.400
I GOT OUT OF HERE,
AND I EXPLORED THE WORLD,

03:19.433 --> 03:21.066
AND I GOTTA TELL YOU,
THERE IS MORE TO LIFE

03:21.100 --> 03:22.734
THAN JUST AMBLING DOWN
MAIN STREET

03:22.767 --> 03:24.233
SUCKING ON YOUR SOFT-SERVE.

03:24.266 --> 03:26.400
- OH, THE SCREAMING CONE
GOT NEW MIX-INS.

03:26.433 --> 03:28.066
- OH, UGH!
- FRESH PEACHES.

03:28.066 --> 03:29.600
IT'S GOOD NEWS.
- I JUST NEVER FIT IN HERE.

03:29.600 --> 03:30.700
YOU KNOW THAT, MAGS.
- ♪ CELEBRATE ♪

03:30.734 --> 03:32.133
- I JUST DIDN'T...
- ♪ CELEBRATE ♪

03:32.166 --> 03:34.600
- FIT IN HERE.
- ♪ CELEBRATE ME HOME ♪

03:34.600 --> 03:36.133
YOU FIT IN HERE.

03:36.166 --> 03:38.300
♪ CELEBRATE ♪
- OH, I CAN'T RESIST.

03:38.333 --> 03:40.633
♪ CELEBRATE, CELEBRATE ♪
- OKAY, KEEP DOING THAT.

03:40.667 --> 03:42.400
- ♪ ME HOME ♪
- I'M GONNA GO LOW. HERE WE GO.

03:42.433 --> 03:44.133
♪ WELL I'M FINALLY HERE ♪
- ♪ WON'T YOU CELEBRATE ♪

03:44.166 --> 03:45.467
- ♪ BUT I'M BOUND TO ROAM ♪
- ♪ CELEBRATE ♪

03:45.500 --> 03:48.200
- ♪ COME ON ♪
both: ♪ CELEBRATE ME HOME ♪

03:48.200 --> 03:50.233
- ♪ COME ON, DADDY, CELEBRATE ♪
- ♪ WELL, I'M FINALLY HERE ♪

03:50.266 --> 03:51.567
♪ BUT I'M BOUND TO ROAM ♪
- ♪ WOULD YOU CELEBRATE ♪

03:51.600 --> 03:53.734
- ♪ COME ON ♪
both: ♪ CELEBRATE ♪

03:53.767 --> 03:57.166
- ♪ THESE BOOBS,
GOT TO CELEBRATE ♪

03:57.200 --> 03:58.500
♪ GOT TO ♪
both: ♪ CELEBRATE ♪

03:58.533 --> 04:00.333
♪ GOT TO CELEBRATE ♪

04:00.367 --> 04:01.467
- ♪ THESE BOOBS ♪

04:01.467 --> 04:04.000
♪ WE CELEBRATE ♪
- SORRY, EMMA.

04:04.033 --> 04:05.200
- ♪ CAN I CELEBRATE ♪

04:05.200 --> 04:06.400
- EMMA, JUST STOP.
- ♪ CAN I CELEBRATE ♪

04:06.433 --> 04:09.400
- EMMA! STOP.
- WHAT? WHAT?

04:09.433 --> 04:11.633
OH, MY GOD.
MARK.

04:11.667 --> 04:13.166
- HELLO, EMMA.

04:13.200 --> 04:14.567
- HEY.

04:14.600 --> 04:16.633
- YOU GUYS JUST FEELING EACH
OTHER UP HERE AT THE STOP SIGN?

04:16.667 --> 04:20.367
- OH, NO, WE--I WAS JUST USING
MAGGIE'S BOOB AS A MICROPHONE.

04:20.400 --> 04:22.100
- SURE, LIKE YOU DO.

04:22.100 --> 04:24.100
OH, MAGS,
TINA'S NOT FEELING WELL,

04:24.100 --> 04:25.533
SO SHE'S NOT GONNA MAKE IT
TO THE SHOWER.

04:25.567 --> 04:27.500
- OKAY, I'LL SAVE HER A CUPCAKE.
- THANKS.

04:27.533 --> 04:29.400
- WHO'S TINA?
- MY WIFE.

04:29.433 --> 04:30.500
- OH, YOU'RE MARRIED?
- YEAH.

04:30.533 --> 04:32.100
- OH, GOD.
OKAY.

04:32.133 --> 04:33.667
THIS ONE DIDN'T TELL ME.

04:33.700 --> 04:38.367
SO I JUST--GOD, THAT'S--
CONGRATS AND MAZELS TO YOU GUYS.

04:38.400 --> 04:40.367
IT'S NOT TINA STEIGERMAN
FROM THE DRILL TEAM, IS IT?

04:40.367 --> 04:42.467
WHO WAS JUST LIKE,
"OH, I BROKE MY ARM AGAIN

04:42.500 --> 04:44.633
'CAUSE I GOT THE BONES
OF A BIRD," SNAP!

04:44.633 --> 04:46.367
REMEMBER?
WE CALLED HER "BIRD BONES."

04:46.367 --> 04:49.066
IT'S SO--

04:49.100 --> 04:51.266
OH, GOD, IT IS.
IT'S THAT SAME TINA.

04:51.300 --> 04:53.200
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
CONGRATULATIONS.

04:53.233 --> 04:54.500
SHE WAS SO NICE.

04:54.533 --> 04:56.033
- OKAY, WELL--
- SHE IS NICE.

04:56.066 --> 04:57.133
I'M ASSUMING SHE'S STILL...

04:57.133 --> 04:58.133
- YEAH.
- WITH US.

04:58.133 --> 04:59.133
- SHE'S WITH US.

04:59.133 --> 05:02.433
WELL, IT'S GOOD
TO SEE YOU, EM.

05:02.467 --> 05:03.633
- YES, AND A GOOD DAY TO YOU,
SIR.

05:03.667 --> 05:05.000
- TAKE CARE.
- [clicks tongue]

05:05.033 --> 05:08.033
SO--I DON'T KNOW WHY.

05:08.066 --> 05:12.000
- I'M GONNA GO.
- OKAY.

05:12.033 --> 05:13.200
- WELL, I THINK
THAT WENT GREAT.

05:13.233 --> 05:14.200
- REALLY?

05:14.233 --> 05:15.400
I JUST TIPPED
AN INVISIBLE CAP

05:15.433 --> 05:17.567
TO THE MAN
I LOST MY VIRGINITY TO.

05:17.600 --> 05:20.333
SO WHY DON'T YOU
DRIVE ME ON HOME?

05:20.367 --> 05:22.367
- YES, MA'AM.
[clicks tongue]

05:25.033 --> 05:27.400
- MAGS, THE HOUSE
LOOKS JUST THE SAME.

05:27.400 --> 05:29.400
IS THAT THE PORCH SWING
YOUR DAD BUILT?

05:29.400 --> 05:30.767
- YEAH, WE BROUGHT IT AROUND
TO THE FRONT.

05:31.000 --> 05:32.100
- OH, I LOVE IT.

05:32.133 --> 05:33.667
- HEY, SHANGHAI.
- BRUCE!

05:33.700 --> 05:35.166
- GET OVER HERE.
- OH, MAN.

05:35.166 --> 05:37.000
OH, I WANT ONE
OF YOUR BEAR HUGS.

05:37.033 --> 05:38.500
- WAIT A SECOND. WAIT A SECOND.
- WHAT?

05:38.533 --> 05:40.166
- ARE THEY NOT FEEDING YOU
IN CHINA, YOU SKINNY MARINK?

05:40.166 --> 05:41.433
- OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT IT IS?

05:41.467 --> 05:43.333
THEY ARE WORKING ME, LITERALLY,
TO THE BONE.

05:43.367 --> 05:45.667
- IT'S THE DIFFERENT SAUCES.
THEY GOT DIFFERENT SAUCES THERE,

05:45.700 --> 05:47.166
AND IT WREAKS HAVOC
ON THE PLUMBING.

05:47.166 --> 05:48.600
- OH, BABE, CAN WE NOT--
- NO, IT REALLY DOESN'T.

05:48.633 --> 05:50.000
AND BE HONEST WITH ME.
- YEAH.

05:50.033 --> 05:51.700
- DID THOSE SAUCES
TAKE YOUR BUTT BY STORM?

05:51.700 --> 05:53.300
- BABE.
- NO, CAN I JUST SAY?

05:53.333 --> 05:55.033
THEY ACTUALLY DID
TAKE MY BUTT BY STORM.

05:55.033 --> 05:56.433
- I KNEW IT.
- IT'S REAL.

05:56.467 --> 05:58.100
I DIDN'T HAVE THE WORDS, I
DIDN'T HAVE THAT PHRASE, BUT...

05:58.133 --> 05:59.500
- I'M GONNA TELL YOU WHAT IT IS.
- THAT'S WHAT WAS HAPPENING.

05:59.533 --> 06:00.667
- THEY HAVEN'T DEFINED
WHETHER OR NOT

06:00.700 --> 06:02.300
THESE ARE SWEET SAUCES
OR SOUR SAUCES, OKAY?

06:02.333 --> 06:04.000
- RIGHT, AND YOU'RE MIXING 'EM.
- YOU'RE MIXING 'EM UP.

06:04.033 --> 06:05.266
- AND IT BECOMES LIKE A...
- ALL OF A SUDDEN--

06:05.300 --> 06:06.433
- MR. WIZARD SITUATION.
- YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?

06:06.467 --> 06:08.166
- SORRY TO, LIKE,
INTERRUPT THIS REVERIE...

06:08.166 --> 06:09.300
- YEAH, YEAH.

06:09.300 --> 06:10.600
- BUT DID YOU FINISH
THE CRIB LIKE I ASKED?

06:10.633 --> 06:12.734
- DAMN IT!
I FORGOT TO DO IT.

06:12.734 --> 06:14.300
- YEAH, ALL RIGHT.
- YEAH. YOU KNOW WHAT?

06:14.333 --> 06:15.734
I'M GONNA GO DOWN
IN MY MAN CAVE,

06:15.734 --> 06:17.734
I'M GONNA FINISH IT UP RIGHT
NOW, AND YOU SHOULD GO INSIDE

06:17.734 --> 06:19.734
AND SEE WHAT YOUR WEIRD BROTHER
DID TO THE PLACE.

06:19.767 --> 06:20.767
- ALL RIGHT, BUDDY.
- OKAY, WELCOME HOME!

06:21.000 --> 06:22.066
- IT'S SO GOOD TO SEE YOU.

06:22.100 --> 06:23.200
- OKAY, THANK YOU.
- I GOT IT. I GOT IT.

06:23.200 --> 06:24.200
COME ON.
- THANK YOU.

06:24.200 --> 06:26.333
- ALL RIGHT.

06:28.300 --> 06:29.500
- TO THE LEFT, MY LADY.

06:29.533 --> 06:31.200
- OH, MY GOD.

06:31.200 --> 06:32.734
WHAT IS THIS
WOODLAND WONDERLAND?

06:32.767 --> 06:34.066
- DO YOU LIKE IT?

06:34.100 --> 06:36.467
- DO I--
IS THIS A HEDGEHOG CUPCAKE?

06:36.500 --> 06:38.567
I'M GONNA PUNCH YOU
IN THE FACE RIGHT NOW.

06:38.600 --> 06:40.533
- IT WAS ALL ZACH.
- THANK YOU.

06:40.567 --> 06:42.567
I TAKE WALKS IN THE FOREST
WHEN I NEED TO THINK,

06:42.600 --> 06:44.266
AND THAT'S WHERE
I GOT MY INSPIRATION.

06:44.300 --> 06:45.600
- IF YOU HADN'T
SEXUALLY HARASSED ME

06:45.633 --> 06:47.033
ALL THROUGH HIGH SCHOOL...
[cell phone chimes]

06:47.066 --> 06:48.467
I WOULD ASSUME YOU
WERE A STONE-COLD GAY MAN.

06:48.467 --> 06:50.233
- I'M GONNA TAKE THAT
AS A COMPLIMENT.

06:50.266 --> 06:51.233
- HOLD ON.
- WHAT IS WRONG?

06:51.266 --> 06:52.300
- NOTHING.
IT'S JUST WORK.

06:52.333 --> 06:53.567
I GOT TO--
- UH-HUH.

06:53.600 --> 06:55.567
- I HAVE A BIG PRESENTATION
THAT JUST GOT MOVED UP,

06:55.600 --> 06:57.066
SO I GOT TO DO IT TONIGHT,
BUT--

06:57.100 --> 06:58.767
- NO, THIS IS THE ONLY WEEKEND
YOU'VE ASKED OFF FOR

06:59.000 --> 07:00.166
IN THREE YEARS.

07:00.200 --> 07:01.567
- I KNOW, BUT YOU'RE
NOT EVEN GONNA NOTICE.

07:01.600 --> 07:03.200
- I'M NOTICING RIGHT NOW.
- NO, BECAUSE YOU KNOW WHAT?

07:03.233 --> 07:04.500
I'M GONNA DO IT AT NIGHT
WHEN YOU'RE SNUGGLED UP

07:04.533 --> 07:06.000
LIKE A BUG IN A RUG
GROWING THIS HUMAN.

07:06.033 --> 07:07.266
ALL RIGHT?
- OKAY.

07:07.300 --> 07:09.000
- WILL YOU MAKE ME
A FLUFFERNUTTER, PLEASE?

07:09.033 --> 07:10.100
- YES.
- THANK YOU. [slaps]

07:10.133 --> 07:12.633
- HEY.
- IT'S GOOD FROM BEHIND TOO.

07:12.667 --> 07:15.233
HEY, PAN'S LABYRINTH,
GET DOWN OFF THAT STEP STOOL.

07:15.266 --> 07:17.266
I GOT TO TALK TO YOU.
- SURE.

07:17.300 --> 07:19.000
I JUST NEED
TO ASK YOU ONE QUESTION.

07:19.033 --> 07:20.000
- WHAT?

07:20.033 --> 07:21.734
- DO YOU NOTICE ANYTHING?
- NO.

07:21.767 --> 07:24.266
- I GAINED 15 POUNDS
SINCE LAST WE MET.

07:24.300 --> 07:25.600
- WELL, IT DOESN'T SHOW.

07:25.633 --> 07:27.133
- WELL, THAT'S BECAUSE
IT'S ALL IN MY THIGHS.

07:27.166 --> 07:30.100
- THAT'S WHERE A WOMAN
GAINS WEIGHT, JUST FYI.

07:30.133 --> 07:32.633
- WELL, JUST FYI,
THAT'S WHERE I GAIN WEIGHT TOO.

07:32.633 --> 07:34.533
- COULD YOU JUST TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH THE VIDEO?

07:34.567 --> 07:37.000
- YEAH.
I JUST GOTTA KEN BURNS IT.

07:37.000 --> 07:39.033
- KEN BUR--WHAT?
THE SHOWER'S IN TWO HOURS.

07:39.066 --> 07:40.200
- HEY, THEY HAVE APPLE TV.

07:40.233 --> 07:42.400
ALL I DO IS CONNECT MY LAPTOP
TO THEIR WI-FI,

07:42.400 --> 07:44.233
ALTHOUGH I WOULD FEEL
MORE COMFORTABLE

07:44.266 --> 07:47.066
IF WE HAD A CODE WORD
FOR WHEN TO START.

07:47.100 --> 07:48.734
- OKAY, FINE, WHAT DO YOU
WANT THE CODE WORD TO BE?

07:48.767 --> 07:51.533
- TORNADO.
- UGH. I CAN'T--

07:51.567 --> 07:54.400
[indistinct chatter]

07:54.400 --> 07:56.700
- I JUST FELT A KICK.
- AWW!

07:56.734 --> 07:58.367
- MAGS, BRUCE'S MOM IS HERE.

07:58.400 --> 08:01.567
- HIDE THE BOOZE!
- OH!

08:01.600 --> 08:04.300
- IN FRONT OF YOU,
YOU'LL SEE DIAPERS LOADED

08:04.333 --> 08:07.000
WITH MELTED CHOCOLATE,
SIMULATING POOP.

08:07.033 --> 08:08.667
YOU CAN SNIFF IT,
YOU CAN LICK IT.

08:08.700 --> 08:11.433
JUST SCREAM OUT WHAT KIND
OF CHOCOLATE IT IS.

08:11.467 --> 08:13.734
EVERYBODY READY?
START SNIFFIN'!

08:13.767 --> 08:15.166
- OKAY.
- OH, GOD.

08:15.200 --> 08:16.734
- IS IT A MR. GOODBAR?
- THIS IS DELICIOUS.

08:17.000 --> 08:18.367
- TAKE 5.
- IS THIS A KRACKEL?

08:18.400 --> 08:19.433
[cell phone rings]
- YEP.

08:19.433 --> 08:21.166
- IS THIS--OH.
- NESTLE CRUNCH.

08:21.166 --> 08:22.467
- DON'T YOU DARE ANSWER
THAT PHONE.

08:22.500 --> 08:24.133
- OH, MY GOD, LISTEN.
KEEP SNIFFIN', TOM SELLECK.

08:24.166 --> 08:25.367
YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

08:25.400 --> 08:27.133
- GOOBERS.
- IT'S NUTRAGEOUS!

08:27.166 --> 08:28.567
- MILKY WAY MIDNIGHT.
- MOUNDS!

08:28.567 --> 08:30.433
- NO.
- OH, MY GOD.

08:30.467 --> 08:32.467
THIS IS REAL POOP.

08:32.500 --> 08:33.667
[laughs]

08:33.700 --> 08:35.066
JUST KIDDING, YOU GUYS.
ALMOND JOY.

08:35.100 --> 08:36.100
- FIVE MORE SECONDS, LADIES.

08:36.133 --> 08:37.266
- A SNICKERS.
SNICKERS!

08:37.300 --> 08:38.633
- COOKIES 'N' CREME.
- I GOT A NUT.

08:38.667 --> 08:40.033
- EMMA.
- SNO-CAPS!

08:40.033 --> 08:42.500
- CORRECT!
DIAPERS DOWN, HANDS UP.

08:42.533 --> 08:45.500
WITH A RECORD-BREAKING NUMBER,
SIX DIAPERS,

08:45.533 --> 08:47.333
ZACH IS THE WINNER!

08:47.367 --> 08:49.767
[applause]
- YEAH, ZACH.

08:50.000 --> 08:51.166
- SORRY.
- THAT'S OKAY.

08:51.200 --> 08:52.400
THERE'LL BE OTHER
DIAPER DERBIES,

08:52.433 --> 08:54.000
PROBABLY NOT MY OWN.
- OKAY.

08:54.033 --> 08:55.333
- SO I'LL JUST HAVE
TO STRUGGLE ON, I GUESS.

08:55.367 --> 08:57.033
- ALL RIGHT, I HAVE A LITTLE
SOMETHING THAT'S GONNA

08:57.066 --> 09:00.500
MAKE THIS CHOCOLATE FROWN
TURN UPSIDE DOWN.

09:00.533 --> 09:02.200
ALL RIGHT, MARY PAT,
MAY I HAVE THE FLOOR?

09:02.200 --> 09:03.467
- OF COURSE.

09:03.467 --> 09:05.467
- ALL RIGHT, IF I COULD
HAVE EVERYBODY'S ATTENTION.

09:05.467 --> 09:07.066
TORNADO.

09:07.066 --> 09:10.000
WE HAVE A LITTLE
SOMETHING SPECIAL PLANNED.

09:10.033 --> 09:11.233
ZACH, TORNADO.

09:11.266 --> 09:14.333
- [whispers] WHY DO YOU JUST
KEEP SAYING "TORNADO"?

09:14.333 --> 09:15.500
OH, RIGHT.

09:15.533 --> 09:18.133
- THIS IS JUST A LITTLE
AUDIO-VISUAL PRESENTATION

09:18.166 --> 09:19.633
THAT ZACH AND I PUT TOGETHER.

09:19.667 --> 09:23.433
[jazzy trumpet music]

09:23.467 --> 09:25.200
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?

09:25.200 --> 09:26.734
- YOU TOLD ME TO SCORE IT.
- OH, MY GOD.

09:26.767 --> 09:34.100
♪ ♪

09:34.133 --> 09:36.500
- OH, EM,
WHERE DID YOU GET THAT?

09:36.533 --> 09:39.400
- OH, YOU'RE THE SPITTIN' IMAGE
OF YOUR MOTHER.

09:39.433 --> 09:40.467
- YEAH.

09:40.500 --> 09:42.100
- SHE WOULD HAVE
BEEN REALLY PROUD.

09:42.133 --> 09:43.633
♪ ♪

09:43.667 --> 09:45.500
- OH, YEAH.
- OH, MY GOD!

09:45.533 --> 09:46.767
WHOSE BUTT IS THAT?

09:46.767 --> 09:49.166
- SHOW ME THAT JUICY ASS.

09:49.200 --> 09:51.500
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA PUT
UP THERE FOR DADDY?

09:51.500 --> 09:53.400
- WHAT ABOUT
THIS BISCUIT CAN?

09:53.433 --> 09:55.000
- OH, NO.
- YEAH, PUT THAT UP THERE.

09:55.033 --> 09:56.133
- OKAY, WHAT'S HAPPENING?

09:56.166 --> 09:57.734
- I THINK BRUCE'S LAPTOP
IS OVERRIDING MINE

09:57.767 --> 09:58.767
FROM THE BASEMENT.

09:58.767 --> 10:00.133
- WELL, FIX IT.
JUST TURN IT OFF!

10:00.166 --> 10:01.667
- WHAT YOU GOING TO PUT
UP THERE FOR ME, DADDY?

10:01.700 --> 10:04.133
- LET ME SHOW YOU,
SWEET MOMMY.

10:04.166 --> 10:05.367
LET ME SHOW YOU.

10:05.367 --> 10:06.467
- BRUCE!

10:06.500 --> 10:07.767
- MAGGIE!
- OH!

10:07.767 --> 10:09.667
- YEAH, HONEY, I'M WORKING
ON THE CRIB RIGHT NOW.

10:09.700 --> 10:11.767
- WE HAVE TO TURN THIS OFF!
WE HAVE TO TURN THIS OFF!

10:11.767 --> 10:13.066
- BRUCE!
- [screams]

10:13.100 --> 10:14.066
- BRUCE!

10:14.100 --> 10:16.633
WHAT--WHO IS MUNICHMUNCHER69?

10:16.633 --> 10:18.033
- WHO'S WHAT?

10:18.066 --> 10:19.667
- THE WOMAN ON YOUR SCREEN.
WHAT IS HAPPENING?

10:19.700 --> 10:21.033
- I DON'T KNOW.

10:21.066 --> 10:22.266
SHE JUST--
I DON'T KNOW WHO THAT IS!

10:22.300 --> 10:23.533
WHY ARE YOU DOWN HERE?
- GIVE ME ONE OF THESE!

10:23.567 --> 10:25.133
OKAY.
OKAY, OKAY.

10:25.133 --> 10:26.700
- YOU KNOW I'M DOWN HERE!
- YOU HAVE A BONER RIGHT NOW!

10:26.734 --> 10:28.133
A BIG BONER!
- OHH!

10:28.133 --> 10:29.533
- AT BEST, IT'S A SEMI!

10:29.533 --> 10:30.667
I DON'T HAVE A BONER RIGHT NOW!

10:30.700 --> 10:32.300
- SHOULD I TAKE OUT THE CAN?

10:32.333 --> 10:33.533
- OH, GOD!
- OOH!

10:33.533 --> 10:34.700
- I'M SORRY!
PLEASE DON'T LOOK.

10:34.734 --> 10:35.700
- CAN'T UNSEE THAT.

10:35.734 --> 10:37.600
- ZACH! TORNADO!
TORNADO!

10:48.667 --> 10:51.400
[knocking]

10:51.433 --> 10:52.700
- WHO IS IT?

10:52.734 --> 10:54.567
- IT'S YOUR OLD PAL, EMMA.

10:54.600 --> 10:56.433
HOW'S IT GOING IN THERE,
BUDDY?

10:56.467 --> 10:58.066
- PRETTY TERRIBLE.

10:58.100 --> 10:59.266
- YEAH?

10:59.266 --> 11:01.467
OKAY, YOU MAYBE WANT
TO COME OUT AND TALK?

11:01.500 --> 11:04.166
- CAN YOU COME IN?

11:04.200 --> 11:07.533
- UM...OKAY.

11:07.567 --> 11:10.433
I JUST--I DON'T KNOW HOW MUCH
SPACE THERE REALLY IS.

11:10.467 --> 11:12.033
- I KNOW.
I'M HUGE!

11:12.033 --> 11:13.033
- NO, NO, NO, NO.

11:13.033 --> 11:14.166
WE'RE GONNA FIGURE IT OUT.

11:14.166 --> 11:16.233
OKAY, NOW I'M COMING IN.

11:16.266 --> 11:20.467
- THANK YOU.
- OKAY.

11:20.500 --> 11:22.633
DO YOU WANT TO TELL ME
WHAT HAPPENED DOWNSTAIRS?

11:22.667 --> 11:24.066
- OKAY.

11:24.100 --> 11:27.567
WELL, APPARENTLY, THERE IS
A WHOLE ONLINE COMMUNITY

11:27.567 --> 11:32.433
OF WOMEN WHO SPECIALIZE IN
PUTTING THINGS UP THEIR BUTTS.

11:32.467 --> 11:34.600
- AND ARE THEY ALL GERMAN?

11:34.633 --> 11:36.300
- WELL,
THEY'RE NOT ALL GERMAN,

11:36.333 --> 11:39.233
BUT I THINK HE PREFERS GERMANS,
YOU KNOW,

11:39.266 --> 11:41.133
'CAUSE OF THEIR HUSKY NATURE.

11:41.166 --> 11:43.333
- AND DOES HE SEE THEM
IN PERSON?

11:43.367 --> 11:44.667
- NO.

11:44.700 --> 11:47.333
I DON'T KNOW WHY I'M SURPRISED,
YOU KNOW?

11:47.333 --> 11:50.300
IT'S BEEN--IT'S BEEN REALLY BAD
FOR A WHILE.

11:50.333 --> 11:51.600
- MAGS, WHY DIDN'T
YOU TELL ME?

11:51.600 --> 11:53.233
- IT'S EMBARRASSING.

11:53.266 --> 11:56.400
I MEAN, YOU'RE OVER THERE
IN SHANGHAI HOBNOBBING

11:56.433 --> 11:58.734
WITH ASIAN HIGH ROLLERS,
TRADING, I DON'T KNOW,

11:58.767 --> 12:00.734
DIAMONDS FOR
BRIEFCASES OF MONEY.

12:00.734 --> 12:02.467
- WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

12:02.500 --> 12:04.767
- I DON'T KNOW, THAT'S WHAT
HAPPENED IN SKYFALL.

12:05.000 --> 12:07.500
- MY LIFE IS NOTHING
LIKE SKYFALL, OKAY?

12:07.533 --> 12:09.533
DANIEL CRAIG IS
NOT MY BOYFRIEND.

12:09.567 --> 12:11.333
I DON'T EVEN
HAVE A BOYFRIEND.

12:11.367 --> 12:14.266
I DON'T HAVE ANY FRIENDS,
EXCEPT MY ASSISTANT RYUCHI

12:14.300 --> 12:17.433
WHO ONLY GOES TO KARAOKE
WITH ME 'CAUSE HE HAS TO,

12:17.467 --> 12:19.467
AND BECAUSE I DO
A PHENOMENAL MANDARIN VERSION

12:19.500 --> 12:21.266
OF "I DON'T THINK YOU'RE
READY FOR THIS JELLY."

12:21.300 --> 12:24.600
[both laugh]
IT'S PRETTY DEPRESSING.

12:24.633 --> 12:27.266
- I JUST WANTED
TO MAKE A RIGHT CHOICE.

12:27.300 --> 12:28.333
- YOU DID.

12:28.367 --> 12:30.266
YOU MADE THE RIGHT CHOICE
FOR THEN.

12:30.300 --> 12:31.767
ALL RIGHT,
YOU WERE, WHAT, LIKE, 25?

12:32.000 --> 12:33.133
- YEAH.

12:33.166 --> 12:34.734
- YOU KNOW, YOU LOST
BOTH OF YOUR PARENTS.

12:34.767 --> 12:37.133
YOU WANTED SOMEONE SAFE.

12:37.166 --> 12:39.333
- WHAT AM I GONNA DO NOW?

12:39.367 --> 12:42.367
- I DON'T KNOW, BUT I KNOW
WE'RE GONNA FIGURE IT OUT.

12:42.367 --> 12:43.567
OKAY?
- OKAY.

12:43.600 --> 12:46.200
- CAN I HAVE A HUG?
OKAY.

12:47.500 --> 12:50.767
[rustling]

12:51.000 --> 12:52.633
OKAY, UM...
- MM-HMM?

12:52.667 --> 12:54.100
- I DON'T WANT TO ALARM YOU,

12:54.133 --> 12:58.066
BUT THERE IS A SLIGHT
RUSTLING SOUND BEHIND ME.

12:58.100 --> 13:00.734
- OH, YEAH, THERE'S--A
RACCOON FAMILY'S BEEN NESTING--

13:00.767 --> 13:02.066
- WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

13:02.100 --> 13:03.266
- NO, NO, NO.
- THEN WHY ARE WE IN HERE?

13:03.300 --> 13:04.500
- WAIT, DON'T WORRY.
THEY'RE FRIENDLY.

13:04.500 --> 13:06.066
WE JUST ONLY NEED TO WORK
IF THEY MAKE THIS SOUND:

13:06.100 --> 13:07.066
[trills]

13:07.100 --> 13:08.133
[raccoon trilling]

13:08.166 --> 13:10.200
- AAH! OH, MY GOD!
- OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

13:10.233 --> 13:11.233
- I FELT ITS WHISKERS!

13:25.667 --> 13:27.033
OH, MY GOD, THE MEETING.

13:27.066 --> 13:28.066
THE MEETING.

13:28.100 --> 13:30.233
OH, MY GOD.
OKAY, I NEED A BLAZER.

13:30.266 --> 13:31.233
WHERE IS A BLAZER?

13:31.266 --> 13:33.700
OH!
OW!

13:33.734 --> 13:35.400
LAPTOP, LAPTOP, LAPTOP.

13:35.433 --> 13:38.133
JUST CHILL OUT!
SHUT UP!

13:38.133 --> 13:40.200
[spits]

13:40.233 --> 13:42.367
OKAY.

13:42.400 --> 13:43.734
- THIS IS THE RIGHT TIME
TO STRIKE

13:43.767 --> 13:46.133
WITH A CASINO COMPLEX
OF THIS MAGNITUDE.

13:46.133 --> 13:47.500
- I'M SO SORRY
TO HAVE BEEN DELAYED.

13:47.533 --> 13:50.700
THERE WAS SOME, UM,
TECHNICAL DIFFICULTIES.

13:50.700 --> 13:53.033
- AH, EMMA, EXCELLENT.

13:53.033 --> 13:58.200
- SO WHAT WE'RE LOOKING AT,
MR. ZHANG, IS--OOPS.

13:58.233 --> 14:00.433
KNOW WHAT? JUST--I'M SORRY,
HOLD ON FOR ONE SECOND.

14:00.467 --> 14:02.233
I JUST--OOP.

14:02.266 --> 14:03.233
OH, GOD.

14:03.266 --> 14:05.467
YOU'RE SLIPPING AWAY ON ME HERE.

14:05.500 --> 14:07.200
OKAY, BUT WE'RE BACK.

14:07.233 --> 14:08.333
ALL RIGHT, HERE WE GO.

14:08.367 --> 14:09.333
[chuckles]

14:09.367 --> 14:14.700
WITH 805 SLOT MACHINES,
507--50--

14:14.734 --> 14:16.700
IS IT 557 GAMING TABLES?

14:16.734 --> 14:18.533
THAT DOESN'T SOUND RIGHT.

14:18.567 --> 14:19.734
I MEAN, I WOULD LIKE
TO DOUBLE-CHECK IF--

14:19.767 --> 14:21.767
- IF I MAY INTERRUPT.

14:22.000 --> 14:24.033
- YES, PLEASE.
THANK YOU.

14:24.066 --> 14:28.633
- WHEN MY FATHER STARTED
THIS COMPANY IN THE EARLY '20s,

14:28.667 --> 14:32.700
HE WAS...
A SHOE SALESMAN.

14:32.734 --> 14:34.600
- UH-HUH.

14:34.600 --> 14:37.600
- NO,
NOT EVEN A SHOE SALESMAN.

14:37.600 --> 14:40.133
HE JUST MADE SOLES.

14:40.166 --> 14:41.533
- OH.

14:41.567 --> 14:43.700
- AND NOW THIS COMPANY'S

14:43.734 --> 14:47.700
A MULTIBILLION-DOLLAR
CORPORATION.

14:47.734 --> 14:53.066
AND I AM RESPONSIBLE FOR THE
INTEGRITY OF MY FATHER'S NAME.

14:55.233 --> 14:57.500
- [snoring]

14:57.533 --> 14:58.633
- COME ON!

14:58.667 --> 14:59.734
IS SHE SLEEPING?

14:59.734 --> 15:01.033
- I'M SORRY.
WHAT HAPPENED?

15:01.066 --> 15:02.633
I'M SORRY.

15:02.667 --> 15:05.000
- I HAVE NEVER BEEN
SO DISRESPECTED IN MY LIFE!

15:05.033 --> 15:07.500
- OH, I--MR. ZHANG, PLEASE,
MY APOLOGIES.

15:07.533 --> 15:09.500
- THIS DEAL IS OFF.
- OH, NO, NO, NO.

15:09.533 --> 15:11.433
SIR, I--SIR, PLEASE,
I CAN EXPLAIN.

15:11.467 --> 15:13.266
IT WAS JUST A TECHNICAL SNAFU.

15:13.300 --> 15:16.100
AND, MR. ZHANG,
PLEASE DON'T LEAVE THE ROOM.

15:16.100 --> 15:17.400
UGH!
- WHAT WAS THAT?

15:17.433 --> 15:19.767
I HAVE NEVER SEEN A DISPLAY
LIKE THAT FROM YOU EVER.

15:20.000 --> 15:21.100
- GRAHAM, I'M SO SORRY.

15:21.133 --> 15:22.433
MY FRIEND'S HUSBAND LEFT HER,
AND I--

15:22.467 --> 15:23.600
- I HONESTLY DON'T CARE.

15:23.633 --> 15:25.066
JUST GET YOURSELF ON A PLANE
TO SHANGHAI

15:25.100 --> 15:26.100
AND FIX THIS NOW!

15:26.133 --> 15:27.200
- SHE'S LITERALLY
FALLING APART.

15:27.233 --> 15:30.367
- EMMA, IF YOU ARE NOT
ON THAT PLANE,

15:30.367 --> 15:33.166
YOU ARE GONE, UNDERSTOOD?

15:38.100 --> 15:39.500
- YOU MIND TELLING ME
WHAT YOU'RE DOING HERE, SIR?

15:39.500 --> 15:41.500
- OH, MY GOD!
- EMMA?

15:41.533 --> 15:43.667
- MARK, WHAT ARE YOU DOING
CREEPING AROUND?

15:43.700 --> 15:45.300
- MRS. JOHANSSEN FROM NEXT DOOR
CALLED AND SAID

15:45.333 --> 15:47.233
THERE WAS A BROAD-SHOULDERED,
BLAZERED MAN SITTING

15:47.233 --> 15:48.467
ON MAGGIE'S PORCH.

15:48.500 --> 15:50.600
- CAN YOU PLEASE GET
THE FLASHLIGHT OUT OF MY FACE?

15:50.633 --> 15:52.166
- OH, SORRY, YEAH.

15:52.200 --> 15:53.734
WHAT ARE YOU DOING OUT HERE
AT 3:00 A.M. IN THE MORNING?

15:53.767 --> 15:55.433
- I MESSED UP
SOMETHING HUGE AT WORK,

15:55.467 --> 15:57.100
AND I GOT TO WAKE UP MAGGIE

15:57.133 --> 15:58.533
AND TELL HER
THAT I HAVE TO LEAVE LIKE--

15:58.567 --> 16:00.266
AND I CAN'T STAY
LIKE I PROMISED.

16:00.266 --> 16:04.433
AND I'M JUST--I AM FEELING
LIKE--LIKE THE WORST PERSON.

16:04.467 --> 16:07.500
- WELL, YOU KIND OF ARE.
- I'M SORRY?

16:07.533 --> 16:09.533
- IF THAT HAPPENED
TO MY BEST FRIEND, I'D STAY.

16:09.567 --> 16:11.367
- OKAY,
I DON'T THINK YOU UNDERSTAND.

16:11.400 --> 16:13.533
I'VE BEEN WORKING FOR THIS
COMPANY FOR THE PAST 11 YEARS.

16:13.567 --> 16:15.100
- THEY CAN'T GIVE YOU
A COUPLE DAYS OFF?

16:15.133 --> 16:16.266
- NO, YOU KNOW WHAT?

16:16.300 --> 16:17.633
IT'S A LITTLE MORE
COMPLICATED, OKAY,

16:17.667 --> 16:19.433
THAN SPENDING EVERY SATURDAY
NIGHT TRYING TO FIGURE OUT

16:19.467 --> 16:21.133
WHO THREW THE LAWN FURNITURE
INTO THE RIVERAS' POOL.

16:21.133 --> 16:23.533
- I CRACKED THAT CASE WITH
THE HELP OF A VERY SMALL PIECE

16:23.567 --> 16:25.767
OF RED T-SHIRT FABRIC THAT
BELONGED TO JOFFREY DAVIDSON.

16:26.000 --> 16:27.433
HIS PARENTS WERE
GETTING A DIVORCE,

16:27.467 --> 16:28.533
AND HE WAS ACTING OUT.

16:28.533 --> 16:30.000
SO DON'T TELL ME
ABOUT COMPLICATED.

16:30.000 --> 16:31.133
- OKAY, WHATEVER.

16:31.166 --> 16:32.734
- OH, THAT'S--
OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

16:32.767 --> 16:35.533
DO WHATEVER YOU WANT
LIKE YOU ALWAYS HAVE.

16:35.533 --> 16:38.233
- YOU GONNA GO MUNCH
ON A DOUGHNUT?

16:38.266 --> 16:41.033
GET THAT OUT OF MY FACE.
I'LL CALL THE REAL POLICE.

16:41.066 --> 16:42.033
- GUESS WHO'S GONNA
ANSWER THE PHONE.

16:42.066 --> 16:43.300
- WHO?
- HELLO? ME.

16:43.333 --> 16:46.033
- I CAN'T.
I JUST CAN'T.

16:48.333 --> 16:49.533
- HEY.

16:49.567 --> 16:51.433
- MORNIN', SLEEPYHEAD.
- MORNIN'.

16:51.433 --> 16:54.100
- POP A SQUAT.
I'M FIRING UP THE FLAPJACKS.

16:54.133 --> 16:56.000
I FIGURED IT OUT.

16:56.033 --> 16:57.633
I ASKED MY BOSS
FOR A COUPLE PERSONAL DAYS,

16:57.667 --> 16:58.633
AND HE SAID, "NO."

16:58.667 --> 17:00.066
SO YOU KNOW WHAT I SAID?

17:00.100 --> 17:01.066
"SCREW HIM," RIGHT?

17:01.100 --> 17:02.433
I'M QUITTING MY JOB.

17:02.467 --> 17:05.400
I'M GONNA MOVE IN HERE AND
HELP YOU TAKE CARE OF THE BABY.

17:05.433 --> 17:07.433
- HEY, GREAT.
THE MORE THE MERRIER.

17:12.633 --> 17:14.233
- WELL, I MEAN, HE CAME OVER
EARLY TO GET SOME STUFF,

17:14.266 --> 17:15.467
BUT THEN HE STARTED CRYING

17:15.500 --> 17:17.300
AND SAYING HOW HE COULDN'T LIVE
WITHOUT ME.

17:17.333 --> 17:20.300
AND THEN I WAS LIKE, "I'M ABOUT
TO HAVE HIS BABY," YOU KNOW?

17:20.333 --> 17:22.133
"I SHOULD TRY
AND WORK IT OUT."

17:22.166 --> 17:24.200
- IS HE GONNA STOP PUTTING
STUFF UP HIS BUTT?

17:24.233 --> 17:25.467
- OF COURSE.

17:25.500 --> 17:27.066
I MEAN, HE'LL PROBABLY HAVE
TO WORK ON IT.

17:27.066 --> 17:28.400
- WORK ON IT?

17:28.433 --> 17:29.767
- OKAY, I DON'T HAVE
A LOT OF CHOICES.

17:30.000 --> 17:31.033
- YOU DO HAVE A CHOICE.

17:31.066 --> 17:32.600
I'LL MOVE HERE.
I WILL HELP YOU.

17:32.600 --> 17:34.166
- THAT IS NOT AN OPTION.
- YES, IT IS!

17:34.200 --> 17:35.633
- YOU COULDN'T EVEN DRIVE DOWN
MAIN STREET

17:35.667 --> 17:37.166
WITHOUT HAVING
A NERVOUS BREAKDOWN.

17:37.200 --> 17:38.734
- OH, MY GOD! SO I'LL JUST TAKE
THE SIDE STREETS.

17:38.767 --> 17:40.433
WHAT IS YOUR POINT?

17:40.467 --> 17:41.500
- HEY, CAN YOU JUST TAKE
IT DOWN A NOTCH, OKAY?

17:41.533 --> 17:42.500
BECAUSE THERE'S RACCOONS
IN THERE

17:42.533 --> 17:43.533
THAT WILL CHARGE AT ANY MINUTE.

17:43.567 --> 17:45.166
- GOOD!
YOU KNOW WHAT?

17:45.200 --> 17:46.734
THEY'RE IN THERE SCREWING
THEIR LITTLE RACCOON BRAINS OUT.

17:46.767 --> 17:48.233
THEY NEED TO KNOW
THAT SOMETIMES LIFE DOESN'T

17:48.266 --> 17:49.567
ALWAYS WORK OUT AS PLANNED.

17:49.600 --> 17:51.500
AND WHEN THAT HAPPENS,
YOU GOT TO BE BRAVE

17:51.533 --> 17:53.266
AND LET YOUR FRIEND HELP YOU.

17:53.300 --> 17:56.066
- BUT MY RACCOON FRIEND LIKES
TO JUMP TRASH CAN TO TRASH CAN.

17:56.100 --> 17:58.266
- OKAY, WHEN HAVE I EVER
JUMPED TRASH CANS ON YOU?

17:58.300 --> 18:00.166
- WELL, THAT'S WHAT YOU DO
WHEN STUFF GETS HARD.

18:00.200 --> 18:02.000
YOU DID IT WITH MARK,
YOU DID IT WITH YOUR MOM.

18:02.033 --> 18:03.367
AND STUFF IS GONNA
GET HARD HERE, EM.

18:03.367 --> 18:06.333
THE SH-- IS LITERALLY
GONNA HIT THE FAN.

18:06.367 --> 18:09.333
AND YOU'RE NOT GONNA BE ABLE
TO SKYPE IN OR CALL RYUCHI,

18:09.367 --> 18:13.100
AND THEN YOU'RE GONNA BAIL,
AND I'M GONNA BE ALL ALONE.

18:13.133 --> 18:15.133
- YOU REALLY THINK
I WOULD DO THAT TO YOU?

18:19.233 --> 18:20.266
ALL RIGHT, YOU KNOW, FINE.

18:20.300 --> 18:21.700
IF THAT'S WHAT
YOU REALLY THINK,

18:21.734 --> 18:23.166
THEN I HAVE A PLANE TO CATCH.

18:23.200 --> 18:25.767
I HOPE YOU ENJOY LIFE
WITH YOUR NEW BEST FRIEND,

18:25.767 --> 18:28.066
MUNICHMUNCHER--WHAT IS IT?

18:28.100 --> 18:30.767
- 69.
- 69!

18:32.767 --> 18:35.767
[One Sunday Morning by Wilco]

18:35.767 --> 18:38.400
♪ ♪

18:38.433 --> 18:41.667
- ♪ THIS IS HOW I TELL IT ♪

18:41.700 --> 18:44.033
♪ ♪

18:44.066 --> 18:47.033
♪ OH ♪

18:47.066 --> 18:51.200
♪ BUT IT'S LONG ♪

18:51.233 --> 18:54.066
♪ ONE SUNDAY MORNING ♪

18:54.100 --> 18:56.266
- HE FINISHED IT.

18:56.300 --> 18:57.266
- ♪ OH ♪

18:57.300 --> 18:59.300
- BABE?

18:59.333 --> 19:00.533
- [sobbing]

19:00.533 --> 19:03.667
- ILKA, PLEASE TRY
TO KEEP IT TOGETHER.

19:03.667 --> 19:05.133
I'M GONNA KEEP
SENDING YOU CHECKS

19:05.166 --> 19:06.700
FOR THAT DEMO YOU'RE RECORDING,
ALL RIGHT?

19:06.734 --> 19:08.433
- YOU DON'T HAVE
TO DO THAT, DADDY.

19:08.467 --> 19:10.133
- DON'T SKIMP
ON A SOUND ENGINEER.

19:10.166 --> 19:12.500
PROMISE ME THAT YOU'LL GET
SOMEONE REALLY SOLID.

19:12.533 --> 19:14.400
IF IT COSTS A FEW MORE BUCKS,
I'LL SEND IT TO YOU.

19:14.400 --> 19:15.533
- YOU'RE PAYING
FOR HER DEMO?

19:15.533 --> 19:16.734
- NO, NO, NO.

19:16.767 --> 19:18.266
- YOU KNOW WHAT IS REALLY
CONFUSING TO ME IS

19:18.266 --> 19:20.467
WHY YOU WOULD PUT TOGETHER
THE WHOLE NURSERY

19:20.500 --> 19:22.600
WHEN YOU ARE CLEARLY IN LOVE
WITH ANOTHER WOMAN.

19:22.633 --> 19:24.100
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

19:24.133 --> 19:25.300
I DIDN'T PUT THE NURSERY
TOGETHER.

19:25.333 --> 19:29.633
- WHO--OH, MY GOD.

19:29.667 --> 19:31.166
EMMA.

19:31.200 --> 19:32.633
EMMA DID IT.

19:32.667 --> 19:33.767
- THAT'S A REAL FRIEND.

19:34.000 --> 19:35.433
AND YOU CAN'T FIND THAT--
- OKAY.

19:35.467 --> 19:40.166
PLEASE SHUT YOUR FACE
AND GET OUT OF MY HOUSE!

19:40.200 --> 19:43.100
[police radio chatter]

19:43.133 --> 19:44.567
- WHAT DID WE DO?

19:44.567 --> 19:46.533
- YOUR DRIVER HAS
AN EXPIRED REGISTRATION.

19:46.567 --> 19:48.100
- AND YOU HAVE
TO DO THIS RIGHT NOW?

19:48.133 --> 19:49.333
- IT'S THE ONE THING I HAVE
TO DO RIGHT NOW, YOU KNOW,

19:49.367 --> 19:50.700
BECAUSE MY JOB'S
SO UNCOMPLICATED.

19:50.700 --> 19:54.033
- MARK,
SHOULD I CALL FOR BACKUP?

19:54.066 --> 19:56.033
IS THAT MAN BOTHERING YOU?

19:56.066 --> 19:58.300
- MRS. JOHANSSEN,
IT'S EMMA CARTER, OKAY?

19:58.333 --> 19:59.533
YOU KNOW ME.
I'M A WOMAN.

19:59.567 --> 20:01.166
- MRS. JOHANSSEN,
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

20:01.200 --> 20:02.433
- NO, YOU KNOW WHAT?
IT'S NOT FINE.

20:02.467 --> 20:03.600
I GET IT, ALL RIGHT?

20:03.633 --> 20:06.133
I'M--I'M A BAD PERSON,
I SCREW UP,

20:06.166 --> 20:08.100
SO I AM OFFICIALLY SORRY, MARK.

20:08.133 --> 20:10.266
I'M SORRY TO ANYONE ELSE
I MAY HAVE HURT.

20:10.300 --> 20:13.066
PAKISTANI MAN, FOR WHATEVER
I MAY HAVE DONE TO YOU.

20:13.066 --> 20:14.200
- WE HAVE NO TROUBLE.

20:14.200 --> 20:15.600
- OKAY, THANK YOU.
- ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

20:15.633 --> 20:17.467
- THANK YOU, MARK.
- WHAT IS GOING ON?

20:17.467 --> 20:18.600
- I ASKED HIM
TO PULL YOU OVER

20:18.633 --> 20:20.500
BECAUSE I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.
- OH, OKAY.

20:20.533 --> 20:22.033
ALL RIGHT, WHAT?

20:22.066 --> 20:23.467
- I LOVE YOU,

20:23.500 --> 20:26.467
AND I WANT YOU TO STAY HERE
AND HELP ME RAISE THIS BABY.

20:26.500 --> 20:28.533
- OH, THIS IS DIFFERENT.

20:28.567 --> 20:30.233
- OKAY, WHAT ABOUT
ALL THAT STUFF YOU SAID

20:30.266 --> 20:31.667
ABOUT HOW I CAN'T HANDLE IT?

20:31.700 --> 20:33.200
- I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU CAN HANDLE IT.

20:33.233 --> 20:35.400
I HONESTLY DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN HANDLE IT,

20:35.433 --> 20:38.333
BUT I DO KNOW THAT YOU ARE THE
ONLY ONE THAT I WANT WITH ME.

20:38.367 --> 20:40.467
OKAY?

20:40.467 --> 20:41.533
- SORRY I'M LATE.

20:41.567 --> 20:42.600
- HONESTLY?

20:42.600 --> 20:44.700
- OH.
OH, MAN.

20:44.734 --> 20:47.433
YOU'D THINK I'D HAVE MORE
CARDIOVASCULAR STRENGTH,

20:47.467 --> 20:50.567
WHAT, WITH ALL THE TRUMPETING
I'VE BEEN DOING.

20:50.600 --> 20:52.033
- EMMA, WHAT DO YOU SAY?

20:52.066 --> 20:55.333
WILL YOU STAY WITH ME
IN MY STUPID TRASH CAN?

20:55.367 --> 20:57.266
- YES.

20:57.300 --> 21:00.700
YES, I WILL STAY WITH YOU
IN YOUR STUPID TRASH CAN.

21:00.734 --> 21:01.700
[applause]

21:01.734 --> 21:03.700
- KISS HER.
KISS HER!

21:03.734 --> 21:05.767
- IT'S NOT LIKE THAT.
WE'RE JUST VERY GOOD FRIENDS.

21:05.767 --> 21:07.066
- I DON'T CARE.

21:07.100 --> 21:09.533
AFTER ALL THAT,
SOMEBODY HAS TO KISS.

21:09.567 --> 21:10.767
- WELL, NOBODY'S GONNA
BE KISSING, SO--

21:10.767 --> 21:13.567
- YEAH.
OH, MY--

21:13.600 --> 21:15.400
- OKAY, ZACH!
- ZACH!

21:15.433 --> 21:16.633
- GIVE THE PEOPLE
WHAT THEY WANT.

21:16.667 --> 21:19.567
- PEOPLE DEFINITELY
DIDN'T WANT THAT.

21:19.600 --> 21:25.000
- ♪ OH, OH, MY FRIENDS ♪

21:25.033 --> 21:29.066
♪ PLEASE,
CELEBRATE ME HOME ♪

21:29.100 --> 21:31.266
♪ GIVE ME A NUMBER ♪

21:49.133 --> 21:52.066
- [screaming]
GET OUT OF THERE!

21:52.100 --> 21:53.767
[raccoons trilling]
GET OUT OF THERE!

21:54.000 --> 21:55.734
OH, MY GOD!
WE DID IT!

21:55.767 --> 21:57.333
WE DID IT!

21:57.367 --> 21:58.700
[screaming]

21:58.734 --> 22:01.000
GET OUT OF THERE!

22:01.033 --> 22:02.266
I FREAKED!

22:02.300 --> 22:04.100
LET'S GO GET A DRINK.

22:04.133 --> 22:06.166
- I CAN'T DRINK.
- I'LL GET YOU THE MILK.
